### Extension name (the extension in question)

aks-preview
### Description of issue (in as much detail as possible)

I'm  facing an issue that i cannot whitelist the onpremise ips using the --api-server-authorized-ip-ranges  feature.  Anything in the reserved  range 10.x.x.x/8 it would seem. 

Looking into this. The docs state onpremise private  ips should be possible, taken from our docs 

- “These IP address ranges are usually address ranges used by your on-premises networks or public IPs. ”

- https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/aks/api-server-authorized-ip-ranges#create-an-aks-cluster-with-api-server-authorized-ip-ranges-enabled

But on the other hand the cli explicitly ignores private ip ranges with the is_global check and throws an exceptions when a 10.,x.x.x range is passed  https://github.com/Azure/azure-cli-extensions/blob/master/src/aks-preview/azext_aks_preview/_validators.py#L131
-	According to the python docs for the lib ip_network. the method is_global method is called is behaving as expected.  It checks the special registry of ip   https://docs.python.org/3.7/library/ipaddress.html#ipaddress.IPv4Address.is_global
-	The 10.x.x.x range is reserved and in the registry so the cli extension will classify this as not public so it will throw an error. The expect exception “"--api-server-authorized-ip-ranges must be global non-reserved addresses or CIDRs” is then thrown   https://www.iana.org/assignments/iana-ipv4-special-registry/iana-ipv4-special-registry.xhtml

The cli extension logic doesn’t seem to make sense here to me. Is this a bug`?

items.body:
### Extension name (the extension in question)
blueprint

### Description of issue (in as much detail as possible)
```
validation error: Parameter 'ResourceGroupDefinition.name' must have length less than 90.
```

This message is received when attempting to execute a blueprint with a `resourceGroup.name` property that is longer than 90 characters, despite that resource group name being a function expression containing `[]` which would ultimately not expand to 90 characters. For instance, the following fails:

```
        "resourceGroups": {
            "ApplicationResourceGroup": {
                "location": "[parameters('l')]",
                "name": "[concat(parameters('u'),'-',parameters('e'),'-',parameters('d'),'-',parameters('a'),'-rg')]"
            }
        }
```

It appears validation is happening directly on the `name` property. It is my belief that it should not be validated if it is an expansion expression, at all, as the CLI cannot know the final expansion.
